records.addlTxt:
Defendant Cornelius L Blain in court with attorney Alejandro A Lockwood.  Kimberly D Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:  

Serve 8 months at the House of Correction, with Huber for work; good time granted; 42 days credit time served.  Court STAYED said sentence and placed defendant on probation for one (1) year.  

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - Pay all applicable surcharges, costs and supervision fees.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;  AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - No contact with the victim, Jose N.;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Job and vocational training;
 - Perform 20 hours community service;
 - Anger management counseling;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Court imposed but stayed 30 days at the House of Correction to be used at the discretion of the agent for any violations.

Court set restitution at zero.

Filed,
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Pretrial Incarceration Credit form.
